cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR 

This paper discusses the challenges and influences of photometric calibration, motion bias, and rolling shutter effect on monocular visual odometry and simultaneous localization and mapping. These topics are closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO). The paper also evaluates the state of the art of direct, feature-based, and semi-direct methods, which involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper proposes possible improvements on existing methods, which may involve graphics (cs.GR).
